# Prep Research Dossier

## Triage

M5 asks the graph projector to gain effect/transition contribution nodes with `consumes` edges, transition mask material slot consumption with typed detail, effect live binding projection through `effect-param` target paths, M5-specific diagnostics, UI repair affordances, browser acceptance, and canary updates — all converging the first three V1 composed examples. The graph vocabulary (`consumes`, `animates`, `binds-live`) and material-slot infrastructure (`CompositionGraphMaterialSlotDeclaration`, `CompositionGraphMaterialSlotBinding`, `GraphMaterialAttachOp`, `VideoEditorTransitionMaterialSlotDescriptor`) already exist from prior milestones, but the projector (`graphProjector.ts`) currently handles only clips, shaders, automations, live bindings, and clipTypes — with zero effect or transition contribution projection. The M0 release-examples doc confirms EX-01/EX-02/EX-03 are not yet composed as graph-backed examples. The root questions are: (1) where exactly in the projector do effect/transition facts enter the graph, (2) how does the existing material-slot infrastructure map onto a typed `consumes` edge for transition masks, (3) what source material already exists across the three canary extensions vs what must be newly composed, and (4) which diagnostic codes and UI surfaces need net-new additions vs reuse.

